values.value:
SET SHADER COLOUR

We can set a Colour-type value for a shader by providing the name of the property, the RGB values and (optionally) an alpha value

SET SHADER FLOAT VALUE

We can set a float-type value by providing the name of the property as well as the desired float value

This example also illustrates how using text and float parameters can make more flexible and dynamic graphs

SET SHADER COLOUR BY HEX

WE can also set a colour-type value by providing the name of the property as well as the 6- or 8-digit hex code for the colour.  This one also demonstrates a gradual shift over time by providing a number to Value 1

POIYOMI SHADER TRIGGERS

Using the included plugin, we can cantrol animatable properties in Poiyomi shaders on the current scene

Each different function of the plugin has a different trigger name, and uses the value sockets of the Call Trigger node to pass arguments in a common pattern:

Value 1: Transition time, Value 2: unused, Value 3: unused
Text1: Property name, Text 2: New values, Text 3: unused

When a trigger is fired it will try to set the named value for all Poiyomi-driven materials in the scene, so be sure to use renamed shader properties if you want to control them individually

SET SHADER Texture Values

We can set the Scale (tiling) and Offset for animatred or renamed Texture-type properties by specifying the Texture property name, as well as the new X and Y values to apply. One of these also demonstrates providing a transition time to the trigger rather than an instant change 

This example also illustrates how TextConcat can be used to separate out the varaible/editable parts of the trigger for easy access]

HEX <-> DECIMAL CONVERSION To make it easier to work with color values, this plugin generates two dictionaries accessible from the node graph. dectohex is keyed with decimal numers from 0 - 255, the value of each is the corresponding hex representation of that value hextodec is keyed with hex numbers from 00 to FF, the value of each is the corresponding decimal representation of that value The triggers below provide examples showing how to make use of these dictionaries
